  "response": "Infant mortality rate is the number of deaths of infants under one year of age per 1,000 live births in a given year. It is an important indicator of a country's overall health and socioeconomic development. A lower infant mortality rate generally suggests better healthcare, nutrition, and living conditions for infants. Factors that can influence infant mortality include access to medical care, maternal health, vaccination rates, sanitation, and economic conditions.",
